{
  "texts": [
    "(1) Assume e ≥ 2.",
    "For almost all σ ∈ G e K, any finite extension M of K(σ), and any abelian variety A over M, the group A(M) tor is finite.",
    "(2) For almost all σ ∈ G e K, any finite extension M of K(σ), any abelian variety A over M, and any prime number ℓ, the group A(M)[ℓ ∞ ] is finite.",
    "Let A be an abelian variety over a finite extension M of K(σ).",
    "Using Weil restriction for abelian varieties [JP22, Lemma 6.1], we know that B = Res M/K(σ) (A) is an abelian variety over K(σ) and A(M) ∼ = B(K(σ))."
  ]
}